title: 820-3023 - Three beeps.
message:
As in subject, board just gives three ram beeps.

If I heat up around U7600, the board works fine until it cools down again.

When hot, I get power at L5550 & C1724, as soon as it cools though, no power there.

C7602::2 measures 0.000 in diode mode.

title: 820-3023 - Three beeps.
message: If C7602 was really shorted it would fry R7601 of course. What is L5550?

title: 820-3023 - Three beeps.
message:
[QUOTE="dukefawks, post: 23957"]If C7602 was really shorted it would fry R7601 of course. What is L5550?[/QUOTE]

Sorry, I mean L7550

R7601 seems to measure correctly at 2.2ohms.


Edit: I don't think C7602 is shorted, I think something on the ::2 side is shorted. If I put the probe on ::1 I get a mostly normal reading.

title: 820-3023 - Three beeps.
message:
Uhm, please look at pin 2 of C7602 and tell me where that is going....

If it beeps is there 1.35V on L7630? If yes then this thing has either bad RAM or cracked balls/traces which is pretty hopeless on these.
